Implementation - Create BST
In this section, we will learn how to make a BST from an array of numbers given to us.

Note - We take the first element of the array as our root so the tree might not always be balanced.

We have made the first element as our node, now for inserting the rest of the nodes the logic followed is (the process always starts from the root):

If the element is smaller than the root
If the left child of root is null, the new node is inserted there and the process is terminated.
Else our root pointer is updated to the left child and the process is repeated from start taking this left child as root (we do this because the element is smaller than the root, so it is bound to be inserted in the left subtree)
If the element is larger than the root
If the right child of root is null, the new node is inserted there and the process is terminated.
Else our root pointer is updated to the right child and the process is repeated from start taking this right child as root
